Thailand Stocks: PTT, PTT Exploration, Sri Trang, Thai Rubber

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-08-05T09:46:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-05/advanced-info-ratchaburi-siam-city-thailand-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies had
unusual moves in  Thailand  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 4:30 p.m. close in Bangkok.  The SET Index slid 30.63 points, or 2.7 percent, to
1,093.38, the largest drop since Jan. 24. The gauge fell 3.5
percent this week, the first decline in three weeks.  Energy companies:  PTT Pcl (PTT)  , Thailand’s biggest
energy company, slipped 2.9 percent to 330 baht, the steepest
decline since June 27.  Thai Oil Pcl (TOP)  , the biggest oil
refiner by market value, sank 5.8 percent to 73.75 baht, the
most since Dec. 16.  Banpu Pcl (BANPU)  , the biggest coal
producer, lost 3.3 percent to 704 baht.  Crude oil fell to the lowest in eight months in  New York ,
set for the biggest weekly decline since May, on speculation
fuel demand will falter as U.S. economic growth stalls and
 Europe ’s debt crisis worsens.  Rubber producers:  Sri Trang Agro-Industry Pcl (STA)  , the
biggest publicly traded rubber producer, slid 6.5 percent to 29
baht, the largest retreat since Jan. 26. Thai Rubber Latex Corp.
(Thailand) Pcl (TRUBB TB) fell 4.5 percent to 5.35 baht, the
most since Jan. 24.  Rubber futures in  Tokyo  dropped the most in almost six
weeks amid growing concern that the global economic recovery is
faltering, reducing demand for the commodity used in tires.  PTT Exploration & Production Pcl (PTTEP)  , the nation’s
only publicly traded oil explorer, declined 4.8 percent to 167.5
baht, the steepest loss since Nov. 24. The company cut its
output estimate for 2011 to 269,000 barrels of oil equivalent
per day, compared with a previous forecast of 273,000 barrels,
said Chief Executive Officer Anon Sirisaengtaksin.  The reduction is a result of delays restarting the Montara
project in  Australia , Anon told reporters in Bangkok today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
